The paper deals with the problem of semantic image segmentation using deep convolutional neural networks (DCNNs) and focuses on weakly supervised and semi-supervised learning. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes Expectation-Maximization (EM) methods for model training, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG and cs.AI). Additionally, the paper evaluates the proposed techniques on the PASCAL VOC 2012 image segmentation benchmark, which is related to multimedia (cs.MM) and information retrieval (cs.IR).
